      "description": "<h3>Company Description</h3><p>Egis is an international player active in architecture, consulting, construction engineering and mobility services. We create and operate intelligent infrastructures and buildings that respond to the climate emergency and contribute to more balanced, sustainable and resilient territorial development. Operating in 100 countries, Egis puts the expertise of its 19,500 employees at the service of its clients and develops cutting-edge innovations accessible to all projects. Through its wide range of activities, Egis is a key player in the collective organisation of society and the living environment of citizens all over the world.</p><p>With 6,000 employees across Middle East &amp; South Asia region, Egis has delivered over 800 complex development projects, stimulating economic growth and enhancing quality of life. Ranked among the top ten firms in the Middle East &amp; South Asia by Engineering News Record (ENR), Egis is committed to sustainable development. The Group’s operations in the Middle East &amp; South Asia are built on strategic acquisitions and a deep understanding of local market conditions. Egis’ long history of providing comprehensive engineering, consulting, and project management services makes it a trusted partner for regional governments, investors, and developers.</p><h3>Job Description</h3><p>We are seeking an Intermediate Civil / Structural Engineer to join our team for a prestigious nuclear project in Mumbai, India. The ideal candidate will bring strong technical expertise, leadership capabilities, and a collaborative approach to ensure the successful delivery of complex design activities. </p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><p><u>Design Responsibilities:</u></p><ul><li>Develop detailed designs under the Architect Engineer scope, including specifications, calculations, drawings, and diagrams, in alignment with applicable codes and standards.</li><li>Review and evaluate designs provided by others to ensure compliance with requirements, interfaces, feasibility, constructability, and Identification of optimization opportunities.</li><li>Ensure designs are feasible, constructible, and optimized for project needs while maintaining compliance with international and European codes and standards.</li><li>Collaborate with multidisciplinary teams to resolve complex engineering challenges and manage interfaces with other disciplines.</li><li>Coordinate with modellers and ensure alignment across design activities.</li></ul><p><u>Additional Responsibilities:</u></p><ul><li>Review the work performed by junior engineers and provide constructive feedback.</li><li>Provide technical support during the design and implementation phases to resolve challenges and maintain quality.</li><li>Develop and maintain direct relationships with contractors to facilitate project progress.</li></ul><h3>Qualifications</h3><p><strong>Qualifications and Skills:</strong></p><ul><li><u>Education:</u> Bachelor's or Master's in Civil Engineering with specialization in Structural Engineering.</li><li><u>Software Proficiency:</u> Experience with software such as Robot, Staad Pro, Navis Freedom, and AutoCAD is required. Knowledge of Ansys would be an added advantage.</li><li>Strong knowledge with applicable international and European codes and standards.</li><li>Proven experience in design of civil and structural engineering projects.</li><li>Excellent problem-solving, organizational, and communication skills.</li><li>Ability to work collaboratively in multidisciplinary teams and manage interfaces effectively.</li></ul><h3>Additional Information</h3><p>Experience in nuclear projects will be considered an advantage.</p>",
