      "description": "<p>Description</p><p>We are looking for self-motivated, reliable candidates ready to begin a career in the Automotive industry at Kendall Ford of Meridian. This is an entry level position providing training and room for growth. Customer service experience is preferred.</p><p><br/></p><p>Some of the benefits of working with Kendall Ford of Meridian are:</p><ul><li>Competitive pay starting at $16.00/hour </li><li>Competitive Paid Time Off and Paid Personal Leave</li><li>Career path development opportunities</li><li>Discounts on parts, service and vehicle purchases for you and your immediate family</li><li>Medical, Dental and Vision insurance</li><li>Paid Life insurance</li><li>401(k) plan with Fidelity</li><li>Accident and Illness supplemental plans</li></ul><p>Our Porters are working in a fast-paced environment, making sure vehicles are arriving and departing to the appropriate store locations. Porters are trusted to drive Kendall vehicles safely and represent the Kendall brand. We offer ample opportunities for career advancement, whether you're interested in service or sales this position will allow you to enter the Automotive industry and find the right career path.</p><p><br/></p><p>Job duties include moving and parking service vehicles as needed, communicating and providing world customer service to service clients, directing service customers to the appropriate advisor, obtaining basic information from vehicles to assist with check in process, retrieving parts and supplies, operating snow removal equipment, washing exterior of vehicles, vacuuming interiors of vehicles and janitorial tasks to keep service drive clean and presentable. A valid driver's license and clean driving record is required.</p><p><br/></p><p>Work is performed equally inside and outside, majority of job duties will be completed via standing or walking, though bending and twisting will occur to enter and exit vehicles frequently. Lifting 20 pounds occasionally, and rarely up to 50 pounds will be required.</p><p>Join Kendall Auto Group and START SOMETHING GREAT! We are a family-owned and operated company with auto dealerships in Idaho, Oregon, Montana, Washington and Alaska. Kendall has been selling and servicing vehicles since 1937.</p><p><br/></p><p>Our mission at Kendall is simple: To deliver an unrivaled customer experience. Through our highly motivated, knowledgeable and caring team of professionals, we pledge to listen to and respect your needs. Doing the right thing means more than selling and servicing vehicles. Our progressive attitude means being exceptional stewards of the communities we operate in. It means going above and beyond every day for the people who mean so much to us – our employees and customers.</p><p><br/></p><p>Our employees are members of the Kendall family, who share our same goals and passions. Ideal candidates are confident, driven people who are excited to grow and succeed with one of the most successful automotive dealerships in the Pacific Northwest. If you are looking for a rewarding career, we would like to meet you and start something great!</p><p><br/></p><p>To apply, please follow the link to our job board site.</p>",
