      "description": "Are you a strategic thinker with a passion for leading projects to success? Do you thrive on managing diverse teams and solving complex challenges? If so, we want you to join our dynamic team as a Project Manager! In this role you can join us from every country we have entities. <br/><br/><strong>YOUR MISSION</strong><br/><ul><li><strong>Keep the Clock and Wallet in Check</strong>: Master timeline and budget management to deliver excellence on schedule and within scope.</li><li><strong>Embrace Change:</strong> Drive scope and change management to adapt smoothly to evolving project needs.</li><li><strong>Stay Ahead of Risks:</strong> Manage risks proactively and turn challenges into opportunities.</li><li><strong>Lead the Charge:</strong> Coordinate and inspire your project team to achieve outstanding results.</li><li><strong>Be the Data Keeper</strong>: Take charge of reporting, documenting, and keeping everyone in the loop.</li><li><strong>Precision Billing:</strong> Ensure invoicing processes are seamless and accurate.</li><li><strong>Be the Communication Champion</strong>: Build strong relationships with stakeholders, customers, and partners while keeping everyone informed.</li><li><strong>Collaborate to Elevate</strong>: Work closely with consultants, project groups, and customer project managers.</li><li><strong>Optimize Resources:</strong> Balance the art and science of resource management for peak performance.</li></ul><strong>MUST HAVES:</strong><br/><ul><li><strong>Leadership Wizardry</strong>: Strong leadership, communication, and interpersonal skills that bring teams together.</li><li><strong>Juggling Master:</strong> Proven ability to manage multiple projects like a pro.</li><li><strong>Problem-Solving Innovator:</strong> Proficient in risk management and finding creative solutions.</li><li><strong>Objective Achiever:</strong> Ability to identify and prioritize key objectives for successful project outcomes.</li><li><strong>Planning Guru</strong>: A knack for forming clear and actionable work plans from diverse requirements.</li><li><strong>Language Skills</strong>: German full professional proficiency is absolutely mandatory as well as English.</li></ul> <br/><strong>NICE TO HAVES:</strong><br/><ul><li>ITIL4 Foundation I IPMA C I PMP I Prince or similar project management fundamentals training </li></ul><strong>FOR YOU</strong><br/>We could tell you all about the free fruit and drinks in the office, that you will have flexible working hours, 30 days of vacation or that remote work is part of everyday life. <br/>But in our eyes, that's not a benefit, it's standard. Here are some of our benefit offers:<br/><ul><li><strong>Learning &amp; Development Opportunities</strong><br/> - Up to 6 additional days off for personal or professional development<br/> - Log into our online platforms to expand your knowledge or improve your language skills</li><li>Country specific Benefits like for example: one <strong>Social Day</strong> for you to assist in social settings or attend events which help improve our environment</li><li><strong>Bicycle leasing,</strong> the contract and insurance will run through us</li><li>The possibility to choose an <strong>additional benefit</strong> that works for you either a fitness membership, jobticket, insurance or restaurant vouchers </li><li><strong>And many more..</strong> ask us about it!</li></ul><strong>JOIN US</strong><br/>Send us your application, including your salary requirements and earliest possible starting date, directly through our online portal via the \"<strong>Apply for this job</strong>\" button. If you have any questions, please do not hesitate to contact <strong>Jessica Loren Meyer.</strong><br/><em>We ask for your understanding that <strong>MATRIX42</strong> can only accept applications online via the applicant portal in connection with our applicant management system due to the currently valid EU data protection regulations.</em>",
