      "description": "<span id=\"spandesc\"><b>About US:</b>\n<br/><br/>Catalyx is a leading engineering firm specializing in cutting-edge Machine Vision, Robotics, and Serialization\ntechnologies focused on the Life Sciences and Logistics Industry. Our innovative solutions empower industries\nacross the globe, enhancing efficiency and productivity. As we continue to grow, we are looking for a dynamic\nAccount Director - Logistics in the North-East Region to join our team, someone who is passionate about technology\nand its potential positive impact and thrives in a fast-paced, highly matrixed organizational environment and has a\ntrack record in our industries. The Company has delivered substantial solutions for large enterprise accounts.<br/><br/><b>Job Overview:</b>\n<br/><br/>The Account Director - Logistics will be responsible for increasing the scope of our engagement in defined enterprise\naccounts. Some of whom are existing accounts and some you will bring forward from your own network.\nDevelop and maintain strong relationships with high-level decision-makers at enterprise-level accounts. Proactively\nunderstand client needs, challenges, and long-term business objectives. Serve as a trusted advisor, providing\nstrategic guidance and solutions aligned with their specific goals. Foster ongoing communication and collaboration\nto build trust and long-term partnerships.\nIdentify and qualify new enterprise-level sales opportunities within your assigned territory.\nDeliver compelling sales presentations that showcase the value proposition of our products/services. Negotiate and\nclose complex sales deals, ensuring mutually beneficial agreements. Collaborate with internal teams to develop\ncustomized solutions that address client challenges. Manage the sales cycle from initial contact to successful\nsecuring of a purchase order.\nIdeal candidates will possess a proven track records in sales within the Logistics industry across one or more of the\nfollowing solutions areas:<br/><br/>\n1. Logistics control solutions sales.<br/><br/> 2. Logistics operations.<br/><br/> 3. Logistics planning – sales of logistics planning solutions.\nIn addition, experience in Business Consulting sales would be a distinct advantage.<br/><br/><b>Responsibilities and Duties:</b><br/><br/>\nThe ideal candidates will be involved in all aspects of Business Development and solutions selling, including:<br/><br/>\n• Screening potential business deals/opportunities with identified final end user customers &amp; analyzing\nmarket strategies, deal/opportunity requirements, prospect and market potential, and financials.<br/><br/>• Closing new business deals by coordinating requirements; developing and negotiating contracts;\nintegrating contract requirements with business operations.<br/><br/>\n• Developing negotiation strategies appropriate to each nominated account.<br/><br/>\n• Protecting organization's value by keeping all business strategies and technical information confidential.<br/><br/><b>*Remote In the Ohio Valley (IL,IN,OH,PA,WV,KY,TN,and NY)</b></span><br/><span id=\"spanreq\"><h3>Requirements</h3><b>Qualifications:</b><br/><br/>\n• A strong and current network in Logistics Control or Resource Planning Solutions and / or Logistics\nOperations in large scale enterprises.<br/><br/>\n• At minimum 5 years of experience of successful selling of relevant solutions and services within the\nLogistics environments at Enterprise Level.\n<br/><br/>• Ideal skillset includes history of Meeting/Exceeding Sales Goals, Strong Prospecting, Presentation, and\nClosing Skills; Sales Planning, Selling to Customer Needs (Solution Selling), Territory Management,\nMarket Knowledge of the Life Science Industry, Self-Motivation for Sales/Results, High Energy Level,\nand Professionalism.<br/><br/>\n• Bachelors / Master’s degree in Supply Chain Management, Business Administration, Technical\nMarketing or MIS or related IT degrees.\n• Strong technical writing, communication, and presentation skills.<br/><br/>\n• Experience with typical off-the-shelf CRM software and other software packages such as Microsoft\nWord, Access, Excel, and PowerPoint.<br/></span><br/><span id=\"spanben\"><h3>Benefits</h3><span><span><b>Why Join Catalyx?</b></span><span><br/></span></span><span><span><br/></span></span><span><span>At Catalyx we understand that our people are our greatest asset and are an integral part of our success. For this reason and many others, we take care of our people. The</span></span><span><span><span> </span></span></span><span><span>team</span></span><span><span><span> </span></span></span><span><span>in Catalyx benefits from a Total Rewards package. This includes excellent personal benefits, competitive salaries, a high-energy work environment, professional growth opportunities, and much more!</span><span><br/></span></span><span><span><br/></span></span><span><span><span>An example of what is offered to our</span></span><span><span><span> </span></span></span><span><span>team</span></span><span><span><span> </span></span></span><span><span>members is as follows:</span></span></span><span><span><br/></span></span><ul><li><span><span><span>Competitive compensation with</span></span><span><span><span> </span></span></span><span><span>technical</span></span><span><span><span> </span></span></span><span><span>&amp;</span></span><span><span><span> </span></span></span><span><span>management</span></span><span><span><span> </span></span></span><span><span>growth tracks</span></span></span><span><span><br/></span></span></li><li><span><span><span>Annual performance-based raises and bonuses</span></span></span><span><span><br/></span></span></li><li><span><span><span>401(k) savings plan(s) with company matching.</span></span></span><span><span><br/></span></span></li><li><span><span><span>Paid Time Off Packages Medical, Dental, Life, Short &amp; Long-Term Disability benefits</span></span></span><span><span><br/></span></span></li><li><span><span><span>A structured approach to career and professional development opportunities</span></span></span><span><span><br/></span></span></li><li><span><span><span>Sponsored professional events &amp;</span></span><span><span><span> </span></span></span><span><span>training</span></span><span><span><span> </span></span></span><span><span>programs...and more!</span></span></span><span><span><br/></span></span></li><li><span><span><span>Catalyx is an equal opportunity employer with a strong commitment to supporting and retaining a diverse and talented workforce.​</span></span></span><span><span><br/></span></span></li></ul><br/></span><br/>",
