      "description": "<span id=\"spandesc\"><p>This is a remote position.</p>\n\n    At Softgic, we work with the sharpest minds—those who build, those who love what they do, and those who bring 100% attitude because that's our #Coolture. Join us in our mission to make life easier with technology and become part of our team as a\n    <b> .NET MAUI Developer with Xamarin.Forms Experience &amp; CAD Expertise.<br/></b>\n<br/>\n<b>Compensation:</b>\n<br/>\n<span><span><span><span>USD 20 - 40/hour.</span></span></span></span>\n<br/>\n<br/>\n<b>Location:</b>\n<br/>\n\n\n    Remote (for Argentina, Colombia, Chile, Bolivia, Brasil, Costa Rica, Cuba, El Salvador, Guatemala, Ecuador, Haití, Honduras, México, Nicaragua, Panamá, Paraguay, Perú, Dominican Republic, Uruguay, Venezuela, and USA residents).\n    <br/>\n<br/>\n<b>Mission of Softgic:</b>\n<br/>\n\n\n     In Softgic S.A.S. we work for the digital and cognitive transformation of our clients, aware that quality is an essential factor for us, we incorporate the following principles into our policy:\n     <br/>\n<ul>\n<li><span><span>Deliver quality products and services.</span></span><br/></li>\n<li><span><span>Achieve the satisfaction of our internal and external clients.</span></span><br/></li>\n<li><span><span>Encourage in our team the importance of training to grow professionally and personally through development plans.</span></span><br/></li>\n<li><span><span>Comply with the applicable legal and regulatory requirements.</span></span><br/></li>\n<li><span><span>Promote continuous improvement of the quality management system.</span></span><br/></li>\n</ul>\n<span><b>What makes you a strong candidate:</b></span>\n<br/>\n<ul>\n<li><span>You have <b>3+ years of experience</b> in Xamarin.</span></li>\n<li>You are <b>expert </b>in .NET.<br/></li>\n<li>You are <b>proficient</b> in .NET MAUI (.NET Multi-platform App UI), C#, CAD (Computer-aided design), and Xamarin.Forms.<br/></li>\n<li><b>English</b> - Native or fully fluent.<span><br/></span></li>\n</ul>\n<b>Responsibilities and more:</b>\n<br/>\n\n\n    We are looking for a .NET MAUI Developer with strong CAD and geometry skills to join our team and help complete a partially developed project. The ideal candidate should have a solid foundation in Xamarin.Forms with demonstrated experience transitioning to .NET MAUI, alongside expertise in C#, XAML, and advanced mathematical skills. \n    <br/>\n<br/>\n\n\n    This role requires experience working with CAD drawings and proficiency in creating fillable polygons by identifying intersections of random segments and curves (including conics). You'll integrate into a dynamic team of programmers and contribute significantly to the remaining 40% of the project.\n    <br/>\n<br/>\n\n\n    Responsibilities:\n    <br/>\n<ul>\n<li><span>Collaborate with a team of three other programmers to complete the existing application.<br/></span></li>\n<li><span>Review and understand the current codebase written in C# and XAML.<br/></span></li>\n<li><span>Implement new features and functionalities as per project requirements.<br/></span></li>\n<li><span>Participate in agile development processes, including daily stand-ups and sprint planning.<br/></span></li>\n<li><span>Utilize Jira for task management and communication with team members and testers.<br/></span></li>\n<li><span>Ensure code quality and maintainability through best practices and code reviews.<br/></span></li>\n<li><span>Manage version control using GIT to track changes and collaborate effectively with the team.<br/></span></li>\n<li><span>Assist in the deployment process, leveraging the team's existing experience in this area.</span><br/></li>\n</ul>\n<br/>\n</span>\n<br/>\n<span id=\"spanreq\"><h3>Requirements</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><span>4+ years of experience in cross-platform development, including: <br/></span></li>\n<li><span>3+ years with Xamarin.Forms or similar technologies.<br/></span></li>\n<li><span>1–2 years transitioning to and working with .NET MAUI.<br/></span></li>\n<li><span>Strong skills in C# and XAML, essential for user interface and application logic development.<br/></span></li>\n<li><span>Proficiency in designing and implementing user interfaces for cross-platform applications.<br/></span></li>\n<li><span>Advanced knowledge of CAD systems, including experience creating complex geometries.<br/></span></li>\n<li><span>Solid mathematical background with expertise in geometry and conic sections.<br/></span></li>\n<li><span>Familiarity with development tools such as Visual Studio and version control systems like Git.<br/></span></li>\n<li><span>Ability to work both independently and collaboratively in a team setting.</span><br/></li>\n</ul></span>\n<br/>\n<span id=\"spanben\"><h3>Benefits</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><span>We're certified as a Great Place to Work. <br/></span></li>\n<li><span>Opportunities for advancement and growth.<br/></span></li>\n<li><span>Paid time off.<br/></span></li>\n<li><span>Formal education and certifications support.<br/></span></li>\n<li><span>Benefits with partner companies.<br/></span></li>\n<li><span>Referral program.<br/></span></li>\n<li><span>Flexible working hours.<br/></span></li>\n</ul>\n<br/>\n</span>\n<br/>",
